.nh
.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-peers - Discover peer nodes in your organization


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel peers [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Queries the AceTeam service discovery API to find peer nodes
in your organization. Optionally filter by capability tags.

.PP
Examples:
  # List all peers
  citadel peers

.PP
# Find peers with GPU capabilities
  citadel peers --capability gpu:a100

.PP
# Find online peers with LLM models, include hardware stats
  citadel peers --capability llm:llama3 --online-only --stats


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--capability\fP=""
	Filter by capability tags (comma-separated, e.g., gpu:a100,llm:llama3)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for peers

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output in JSON format

.PP
\fB--online-only\fP[=false]
	Only show online peers

.PP
\fB--stats\fP[=false]
	Include hardware stats (CPU, memory, GPU usage)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
